AB  - According to relevant researches, the participation of private enterprises plays a vital role in boosting the efficiency of PPP projects. However, private enterprises, important parties for social capital, only occupy a relatively low share of PPP market in China. Furthermore, there is a large gap between private enterprises and state-owned enterprises. In response to the low participation of private enterprises, existing researches have explored the barriers of private enterprises to participate in PPP projects from macro-environmental factors, project factors, and government factors. As a result, the economic level of the country, profits and risks of projects, prejudices of the government and the natural monopoly of state-owned enterprises can give rise to the decreased participation willingness of private enterprises. However, since these researches mainly conduct questionnaire surveys or apply methods to specific projects for targeted discussions, they are short of constructing theoretical models and empirical researches. In order to figure out the low participation of private enterprises, this paper interprets cooperative willingness of private enterprises. In other words, this paper regards cooperative willingness as the research object, starts from the perspective of private enterprises, explores the influencing factors and influencing paths of private enterprises' participation, theoretically discusses private enterprises' participation behavior and conducts empirical verification. Based on the Social Exchange Theory and Prospect Theory, this research proposes the relational embeddedness affecting the participation of private enterprises from the perspective of informal contracts and implicit incentives. With the construction of a chained mediation model, this paper explores the mechanism of relational embeddedness affecting cooperation willingness, proposes a dual governance path to solve the low cooperative willingness of private enterprises, namely “relational embeddedness-opportunistic behavior of government departments-cooperative willingness of private enterprises” and “ relational embeddedness-cooperation risks-cooperative willingness of private enterprises”. As for questionnaire surveys, this study distributes questionnaires to employees of private enterprises online and offline, collects 306 valid questionnaires and constructs a structural equation model for hypothesis testing. The research results demonstrate that: (1) The relational embeddedness of public sectors and private enterprises will have a positive effect on the cooperative willingness. (2) The perception of opportunism by private enterprises partially plays the mediating role between relational embeddedness and cooperative willingness. (3) The perception of cooperative risks by private enterprises partially plays the mediating role between relational embeddedness and cooperative willingness. (4) The perception of opportunism and cooperative risks by private enterprises has a chained mediating effect between relational embeddedness and cooperative willingness. If private enterprises and public sectors establish a higher level of relational embeddedness, it can lower the perceived opportunism, reduce the perceived cooperative risks and elevate cooperative willingness. By virtue of empirical analysis, this research reveals the multiple acting paths of relational embeddedness on cooperative willingness with the perception of opportunism and cooperative risks as the mediation, replenishes researches on the antecedent variables of cooperative willingness from informal perspective and recessive motivation, enriches the relevant research literature on cooperative willingness, supplies a new perspective and thought for the theoretical study of PPP, and provides theoretical guidance for enhancing the participation of private enterprises. In terms of practical value, this research proposes a method to solve the low cooperative willingness of private enterprises, which is conducive to deeply and clearly recognizing the importance of relational embeddedness, perception of opportunism and cooperation risks by the public sectors in enhancing the cooperative willingness of private enterprises. Firstly, the establishment of an accountability mechanism can constrain government departments' default behavior through information disclosure in the process of PPP projects, thereby effectively reducing the occurrence of opportunistic behavior of the government and eliminating the perception of opportunism by private enterprises. Secondly, the creation of an information sharing platform and the improvement of information disclosure system can hyalinize and normalize PPP market and eliminate the hysteresis quality and asymmetry of information flow between private enterprises and government departments. Lastly, the construction of a PPP credit system and supervisory mechanism can contribute to preferably regulating PPP market, restricting behavior of both parties, lowering the perception of cooperative risks by private enterprises, and promoting the long-term and stable development of PPP projects. © 2021. All Rights Reserved.
